HmAgentLogSeverity.name: HmAgentLogSeverity
HmAgentLogSeverity.description: Severity code used in determining the SysLog priority value.

hm2LogSnmpLogGetRequest.name: hm2LogSnmpLogGetRequest
hm2LogSnmpLogGetRequest.description: Enable logging of SNMP GET requests.

hm2LogSnmpLogSetRequest.name: hm2LogSnmpLogSetRequest
hm2LogSnmpLogSetRequest.description: Enable logging of SNMP SET requests.

hm2LogSnmpLogGetSeverity.name: hm2LogSnmpLogGetSeverity
hm2LogSnmpLogGetSeverity.description: Define the log severity for SNMP GET requests.

hm2LogSnmpLogSetSeverity.name: hm2LogSnmpLogSetSeverity
hm2LogSnmpLogSetSeverity.description: Define the log severity for SNMP SET requests.

hm2LogCliCommandsAdminStatus.name: hm2LogCliCommandsAdminStatus
hm2LogCliCommandsAdminStatus.description: Administratively enable/disable the logging of the CLI commands.

hm2LogBufferdLogLevelThreshold.name: hm2LogBufferdLogLevelThreshold
hm2LogBufferdLogLevelThreshold.description: Severities at or below this threshold are logged in the buffered log and will not be overwritten by lower priority log messages.

hm2LogSyslogAdminStatus.name: hm2LogSyslogAdminStatus
hm2LogSyslogAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable syslog logging globally.

hm2LogSyslogClientTlsVersions.name: hm2LogSyslogClientTlsVersions
hm2LogSyslogClientTlsVersions.description: The TLS versions supported by the syslog client.

hm2LogSyslogClientTlsCipherSuites.name: hm2LogSyslogClientTlsCipherSuites
hm2LogSyslogClientTlsCipherSuites.description: The cipher suite supported by the syslog client.

hm2LogSyslogServerIndex.name: hm2LogSyslogServerIndex
hm2LogSyslogServerIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the entry in the table and so the syslog server.

hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddrType.name: hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddrType
hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddrType.description: Address type for server IP address. Currently, only ipv4(1) and dns(16) are supported.

hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddr.name: hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddr
hm2LogSyslogServerIPAddr.description: IP address of syslog server for logging.

hm2LogSyslogServerUdpPort.name: hm2LogSyslogServerUdpPort
hm2LogSyslogServerUdpPort.description: TCP or UDP port used for syslog server transmission. If this value is zero then the default port 514 is used.

hm2LogSyslogServerLevelUpto.name: hm2LogSyslogServerLevelUpto
hm2LogSyslogServerLevelUpto.description: Up to log level to be sent to this syslog server.

hm2LogSyslogServerLogType.name: hm2LogSyslogServerLogType
hm2LogSyslogServerLogType.description: Defines the type of log messages to be sent to the syslog server. systemlog (1): Define the system event log entries as stored also in the system event log. audittrail (2): Define the audit trail log entries.

hm2LogSyslogServerRowStatus.name: hm2LogSyslogServerRowStatus
hm2LogSyslogServerRowStatus.description: Syslog server entry status. active(1) - This syslog server is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5)- Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this syslog server entry.

hm2LogSyslogServerTransportType.name: hm2LogSyslogServerTransportType
hm2LogSyslogServerTransportType.description: The transport type used to deliver the log messages to the syslog server. When set to udp(1) the syslog messages are sent over UDP on the configured port. When set to tls(2) the syslog messages are sent over TLS on configured TCP port (hm2LogSyslogServerUdpPort).

hm2LogPersistAdminStatus.name: hm2LogPersistAdminStatus
hm2LogPersistAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable persistent logging globally.

hm2LogPersistMaxFileSize.name: hm2LogPersistMaxFileSize
hm2LogPersistMaxFileSize.description: Maximum persistent logfile size on non-volatile medium in Kbytes (0..4096). If this value is zero logging is disabled.

hm2LogPersistFilesMax.name: hm2LogPersistFilesMax
hm2LogPersistFilesMax.description: Maximum number of persistent logfiles on non-volatile medium (0..25). If this value is zero logging and archiving is disabled.

hm2LogPersistLevelUpto.name: hm2LogPersistLevelUpto
hm2LogPersistLevelUpto.description: Up to log level to be sent to the persistent log

hm2LogPersistentFileTable.name: hm2LogPersistentFileTable
hm2LogPersistentFileTable.description: A list of persistent log files

hm2LogPersistentFileEntry.name: hm2LogPersistentFileEntry
hm2LogPersistentFileEntry.description: An entry of persistent log files

hm2LogPersistentFileName.name: hm2LogPersistentFileName
hm2LogPersistentFileName.description: The name of the log file.

hm2LogPersistentFileSize.name: hm2LogPersistentFileSize
hm2LogPersistentFileSize.description: The size of the file in bytes.

hm2LogCounterOperatingHours.name: hm2LogCounterOperatingHours
hm2LogCounterOperatingHours.description: Cumulated uptime of the device in seconds.

hm2LogCounterFlashTable.name: hm2LogCounterFlashTable
hm2LogCounterFlashTable.description: A list of log counter entries

hm2LogCounterFlashEntry.name: hm2LogCounterFlashEntry
hm2LogCounterFlashEntry.description: An entry of log counter entries

hm2LogCounterFlashBlock.name: hm2LogCounterFlashBlock
hm2LogCounterFlashBlock.description: The name of the flash region.

hm2LogCounterFlashDescription.name: hm2LogCounterFlashDescription
hm2LogCounterFlashDescription.description: The textual description of the group.

hm2LogCounterFlashCount.name: hm2LogCounterFlashCount
hm2LogCounterFlashCount.description: The number of flash sectors in this group.

hm2LogCounterFlashValue.name: hm2LogCounterFlashValue
hm2LogCounterFlashValue.description: The number of sector erase operations performed for this group.

hm2LogTempMinimum.name: hm2LogTempMinimum
hm2LogTempMinimum.description: Minimal temperature on the device in 10th of centigrade (Celsius).

hm2LogTempMaximum.name: hm2LogTempMaximum
hm2LogTempMaximum.description: Maximal temperature on the device in 10th of centigrade (Celsius).

hm2LogTempVariationCount.name: hm2LogTempVariationCount
hm2LogTempVariationCount.description: Number of variations (up or down) by minimum 20 centigrade (Celsius) in maximum one hour period.

hm2LogTempHistTable.name: hm2LogTempHistTable
hm2LogTempHistTable.description: A list of temperature ranges and how many hours the device has been in these ranges (histogram).

hm2LogTempHistEntry.name: hm2LogTempHistEntry
hm2LogTempHistEntry.description: An entry of temperature ranges and how many hours the device has been in these ranges (histogram).

hm2LogTempHistRangeMin.name: hm2LogTempHistRangeMin
hm2LogTempHistRangeMin.description: The lower bound of the range in 10th of centigrade (Celsius).

hm2LogTempHistRangeMax.name: hm2LogTempHistRangeMax
hm2LogTempHistRangeMax.description: The upper bound of the range in 10th of centigrade (Celsius).

hm2LogTempHistTime.name: hm2LogTempHistTime
hm2LogTempHistTime.description: The time spent in this range in minutes.

hm2LogAuditTrailComment.name: hm2LogAuditTrailComment
hm2LogAuditTrailComment.description: Enter a Comment to begin or end a group of entries in the audit trail. Returns an empty string when read.

hm2LogEmailFromAddress.name: hm2LogEmailFromAddress
hm2LogEmailFromAddress.description: Mail address from which the mail has be sent.

hm2LogEmailLogDuration.name: hm2LogEmailLogDuration
hm2LogEmailLogDuration.description: Periodic timer (in minutes) to send an email-alert.

hm2LogEmailUrgentSeverity.name: hm2LogEmailUrgentSeverity
hm2LogEmailUrgentSeverity.description: Log Severity at/below which the email-alert to be sent immediately.

hm2LogEmailNonUrgentSeverity.name: hm2LogEmailNonUrgentSeverity
hm2LogEmailNonUrgentSeverity.description: Log Severity at/below which the log should be saved in a buffer and sent as an email-alert later(In case of log duration timeout / log buffer overflow ).

hm2LogEmailNumEmailsSent.name: hm2LogEmailNumEmailsSent
hm2LogEmailNumEmailsSent.description: Number of email alerts that have been sent successfully.

hm2LogEmailNumEmailFailures.name: hm2LogEmailNumEmailFailures
hm2LogEmailNumEmailFailures.description: Number of email alerts that could not be sent.

hm2LogEmailTimeOfLastMailSent.name: hm2LogEmailTimeOfLastMailSent
hm2LogEmailTimeOfLastMailSent.description: Local system time (hm2SystemLocalTime) when the last mail was sent.

hm2LogEmailAction.name: hm2LogEmailAction
hm2LogEmailAction.description: After configuring all email alert settings, set this object to 'test' to sendt a test message to the configured address(es). Setting the object to 'non-urgent' will force the device to immediately sent all buffered logs to the configured email server(s)/address(es). When read the object is read it always returns 'other'. The object can't be set as 'other'.

hm2LogEmailTestMessageType.name: hm2LogEmailTestMessageType
hm2LogEmailTestMessageType.description: Message type for testing email alert functionality.

hm2LogEmailTestMessageBody.name: hm2LogEmailTestMessageBody
hm2LogEmailTestMessageBody.description: Message body for testing email alert functionality.

hm2LogEmailToAddressTable.name: hm2LogEmailToAddressTable
hm2LogEmailToAddressTable.description: The table listing the destination email address and the message type.

hm2LogEmailToAddressEntry.name: hm2LogEmailToAddressEntry
hm2LogEmailToAddressEntry.description: The table entry listing the destination email address and the message type.

hm2LogEmailToAddrMessageIndex.name: hm2LogEmailToAddrMessageIndex
hm2LogEmailToAddrMessageIndex.description: An integer used only for indexing purposes. Generally monotonically increasing from 1 as new addresses are configured. Re-use of values for this index should be avoided.

hm2LogEmailToAddrAddress.name: hm2LogEmailToAddrAddress
hm2LogEmailToAddrAddress.description: Email address to which the email-alert to be sent.

hm2LogEmailToAddrEntryStatus.name: hm2LogEmailToAddrEntryStatus
hm2LogEmailToAddrEntryStatus.description: Create, change or delete the entry.

hm2LogEmailSubjectTable.name: hm2LogEmailSubjectTable
hm2LogEmailSubjectTable.description: List of subject of the email for particular message type.

hm2LogEmailSubjectEntry.name: hm2LogEmailSubjectEntry
hm2LogEmailSubjectEntry.description: This entry shows what kind of subject to be used for the given message type.

hm2LogEmailSubject.name: hm2LogEmailSubject
hm2LogEmailSubject.description: Email subject for given message type.

hm2LogEmailSubjectEntryStatus.name: hm2LogEmailSubjectEntryStatus
hm2LogEmailSubjectEntryStatus.description: Create, change or delete the entry.

hm2LogEmailMailServerTable.name: hm2LogEmailMailServerTable
hm2LogEmailMailServerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mail servers.

hm2LogEmailMailServerEntry.name: hm2LogEmailMailServerEntry
hm2LogEmailMailServerEntry.description: This entry shows the conmfiguration for the mail server(s).

hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrIndex.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrIndex
hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrIndex.description: An integer used only for indexing purposes. Re-use of values for this index is allowed.

hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrDescr.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrDescr
hm2LogEmailSmtpAddrDescr.description: The description of the server configured.

hm2LogEmailSmtpPort.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpPort
hm2LogEmailSmtpPort.description: SMTP port number. When this object is set to 0, it resets to factory default port number 25.

hm2LogEmailSmtpSecurity.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpSecurity
hm2LogEmailSmtpSecurity.description: This is the authentication mechanism that should be used.

hm2LogEmailSmtpLoginID.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpLoginID
hm2LogEmailSmtpLoginID.description: This user id is used while the switch/router is being authenticated by the SMTP server, if the hm2LogEmailSmtpSecurity is configured to 'tlsv1'.

hm2LogEmailSmtpPassword.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpPassword
hm2LogEmailSmtpPassword.description: This password is used while the switch/router is being authenticated by the SMTP server, if the hm2LogEmailSmtpSecurity is configured to 'tlsv1'.

hm2LogEmailSmtpEntryStatus.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpEntryStatus
hm2LogEmailSmtpEntryStatus.description: Create, change or delete the entry.

hm2LogEmailSmtpTimeout.name: hm2LogEmailSmtpTimeout
hm2LogEmailSmtpTimeout.description: Time out duration (in seconds) before packets are retransmitted.

hm2LogEmailClientTlsVersions.name: hm2LogEmailClientTlsVersions
hm2LogEmailClientTlsVersions.description: The TLS version supported by the email-alert logging client.

hm2LogEmailClientTlsCipherSuites.name: hm2LogEmailClientTlsCipherSuites
hm2LogEmailClientTlsCipherSuites.description: The cipher suite supported by the email-alert logging client.

hm2LogAuditStartNextSector.name: hm2LogAuditStartNextSector
hm2LogAuditStartNextSector.description: A notification shall be sent when the audit trail has filled one sector and starts a new one.

hm2LogEmailSendFailed.name: hm2LogEmailSendFailed
hm2LogEmailSendFailed.description: Whenever a mail sending to the SMTP server is failed, this trap is sent with a count of how many times the connection to the SMTP server is failed so far.
